t\\\":\\\"**Considering test file adjustments**\\\\n\\\\nI need to look into the dynamic report for any uncovered classes, although the user is only using the active class right now. Instead of broadening the scope, should I just add a new file or adjust existing tests? It seems like creating a new test file would be the best option. I also want to consider whether I should avoid using `$` in the top-level test file. Then, I might need to create a commit for these changes.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Reviewing Git Commit Process**\\\\n\\\\nI’m working through the Git commit process and need to ensure I'm only including staged files. I should check the status to see if other files are staged using `git status --short`, which shows my modified file as unstaged. Staging the new file seems fine, but I should also confirm if the build directory is being tracked or ignored. Let's create the file and focus on the path.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_NLn80bn4ravyvlOwD3ad7ftv|fc_08cc2260157aeb9a0169f0ab47a058819e8252943f2ecc35a9\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.openjfx/javafx-base/13-ea/src/test/java/org_openjfx/javafx_base/FieldUtilTest.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_openjfx.javafx_base;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\nimport com.sun.javafx.reflect.FieldUtil;\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\npublic class FieldUtilTest {\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void getFieldReturnsDeclaredPublicFields() throws Exception {\\n        Field field = FieldUtil.getField(DeclaredPublicFieldTarget.class, \\\"displayName\\\");\\n\\n        assertThat(field.getDeclaringClass()).isEqualTo(DeclaredPublicFieldTarget.class);\\n      